Return the node object with id id

If this graph is mutable, the ids of nodes may change as a result of removing nodes or edges. Hence, this method should be used with care to guarantee the expected Node is returned.

remove

public void remove(Node n)
Description copied from interface: MutableGraph
Remove the node node from the graph together with any edges which have an endpoint in node.

  • Subsequent calls to Node.out() for the node will return null.
  • Subsequent use of attribute data for the node will fail with an IndexOutOfBoundsException

    • Specified by:

remove

public void remove(Edge e)
Description copied from interface: MutableGraph
Remove the edge from the graph.

Once the method is complete, the edge's Edge.source() and Edge.target() methods will continue to point to the source and target node objects, but the Edge.edgeId() method will return -edgeId() - 1 and attempts to get or set attributes will fail with an IndexOutOfBoundsException.

moveEdge

public void moveEdge(Edge e,
                     Node u,
                     Node v)
Description copied from interface: MutableGraph
Move an edge specifying the new endpoints.

At the end of this method call, the edge's Edge.source() method will return u, the edge's Edge.target() method will return v, and the edge will be accessible via the appropriate adjacency iteration methods.

This method does not necessarily make an edge directed, an undirected edge will retain the undirected semantics.

Specified by:
moveEdge in interface MutableGraph
Parameters:
e - the edge to be moved.
u - the new source endpoint
v - the new target endpoint.

nodeSize

public int nodeSize()
Description copied from interface: Graph
Returns the number of nodes in the digraph. If the graph is not a MutableGraph, the number of nodes indicates at the same time the range of the node identifiers. If nodeSize() returns s, then
  1. There are s nodes in the graph
  2. Each node has a unique id in the range [0,s)

Specified by:
nodeSize in interface Graph

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Produces a string for the graph in a simple adjacency list representation. Each node n is listed in order (by Node.nodeId()), followed by a colon ':' and a space separated list of the nodes to which n is linked by an edge.
